cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper presents a machine learning approach for appliance event detection, which involves multivariate supervised classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses boosting-oriented adaptive training, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also deals with energy consumption patterns and appliance characteristics, which are relevant to the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
